        <div class="side">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>What you can expect</h3>
            <p><strong>Keynotes</strong> that move a room and land strategically.</p>
            <p><strong>Workshops</strong> with tools teams can use the next day.</p>
            <p><strong>Writing</strong> that sharpens voice and builds authority.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Fast contact</h3>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:kacie.buzzard@gmail.com">kacie.buzzard@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p class="note">For events, include date + audience size + goal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="sec">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>
        I’m a communications leader, speaker, inclusion consultant, and writer with 16+ years of experience building digital engagement
        strategies for global brands, healthcare systems, and mission-driven organizations.
      </p>
      <p>
        My work bridges professional expertise and lived experience—helping teams communicate with empathy, authenticity, and measurable impact
        while elevating disability, caregiver, and neurodivergent voices.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="speaking" class="sec">
      <h2>Speaking</h2>
      <p>Story-driven keynotes that challenge audiences to rethink communication, leadership, and inclusion through a human-centered lens.</p>

      <div class="grid" style="margin-top:14px">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Keynotes</h3>
          <p>Conference sessions designed to connect emotionally and land strategically—grounded in real experience and practical takeaways.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Workshops</h3>
          <p>Interactive sessions for teams: inclusive storytelling, caregiver-aware culture, and communication that earns trust.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Panels & Moderation</h3>
          <p>Disability, caregiving, leadership, and community trust—facilitated with clarity, warmth, and strong audience engagement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="services" class="sec">
      <h2>Services</h2>

      <h4>Speaking</h4>
      <p>Keynotes, conferences, leadership events, and advocacy panels focused on communication, caregiving, and inclusion.</p>

      <h4>Inclusion Consulting</h4>
      <p>Helping organizations authentically engage disability, caregiver, and neurodivergent communities—with accessibility and trust built in.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="writing" class="sec">
      <h2>Writing & Thought Leadership</h2>
      <p>
        Voice, messaging, and narrative systems that make your ideas easier to repeat—and harder to ignore.
        This can include keynote scripts, executive LinkedIn direction, and longform storytelling.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="excerpts" class="sec">
      <h2>The Waiting Rooms of My Life</h2>
      <p>Selected excerpts from my memoir-in-progress—about caregiving, resilience, and the rooms that change us.</p>
      <blockquote>
        I have learned more about myself in waiting rooms than anywhere else in my life. They are places where identity dissolves and survival quietly reshapes you.
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        Caregiving is not a moment of crisis. It is a long negotiation between love, endurance, and systems never designed for you to survive them.
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        Time moves forward. Trauma does not. The hallway changes. The fear remembers.
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="sec">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Speaking inquiries, partnerships, and consulting: <a href="mailto:kacie.buzzard@gmail.com">kacie.buzzard@gmail.com</a></p>

